iao_definition: ['A food which is produced from an organism which has changes in its DNA as a result of genetic engineering.']
rdf_comment: ["LanguaL curation note: 'Genetically modified food' means food containing, consisting of or produced from GMOs - in accordance with REGULATION (EC) No 1829/2003 OF THE EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT AND OF THE COUNCIL of 22 September 2003 on genetically modified food and feed."]
label: ['food (genetically-modified)']

label: ['application']

label: ['Zea mays']

iao_definition: ['A part of an ecosystem where people gather for the purchase and sale of provisions, livestock, and other goods.']
rdf_comment: ['As with campgrounds and fairgrounds, land use is the key differentia here. The regularity of marketplace activities may provide a differentia for further growth of this branch.']
label: ['market']

iao_definition: ['A plan is a realizable entity that is the inheres in a bearer who is committed to realizing it as a planned process.']
label: ['plan']

iao_definition: ['Any of a kingdom (Animalia) of living things including many-celled organisms and often many of the single-celled ones (as protozoans) that typically differ from plants in having cells without cellulose walls, in lacking chlorophyll and the capacity for photosynthesis, in requiring more complex food materials (as proteins), in being organized to a greater degree of complexity, and in having the capacity for spontaneous movement and rapid motor responses to stimulation.']
label: ['animal']

iao_definition: ["A single physical entity inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's quantities or relative ratios of subparts."]
rdf_comment: ['For example calcium composition (which may inhere in bone), haemoglobin composition (which may inhere in blood).']
label: ['composition']

iao_definition: ['A document assembled by an author for the purpose of providing information for the audience. A report is the output of a documenting process and has the objective to be consumed by a specific audience. Topic of the report is on something that has completed. A report is not a single figure. Examples of reports are journal article, patent application, grant progress report, case report (not patient record).']
label: ['report']

rdf_comment: ['"An imperial mass unit which is equivalent to 64.798,91 milligrams." [Wikipedia:Wikipedia]']
label: ['grain']

iao_definition: ['A food product not including meat and animal tissue products (such as gelatin or animal-derived rennet).']
label: ['vegetarian food product']

iao_definition: ['A biological macromolecule minimally consisting of one polypeptide chain synthesized at the ribosome.']
label: ['protein']

iao_definition: ['A spread is a food that is spread, generally with a knife, onto foods such as bread and crackers.']
label: ['food spread']

iao_definition: ['An organic amino compound that consists of amino acid residues (unmodified amino-acid residues and/or modified amino-acid residues) linked by peptide bonds or derivatives of such bonds.', 'An organic amino compound that is a polymer of amino acid chain components (unmodified amino-acid residues and/or modified amino-acid residues) linked by peptide bonds or derivatives of such bonds.']
label: ['amino acid chain']

iao_definition: ['A chicken younger than 10 weeks old (previously younger than 13 weeks), of either sex, that is tender-meated with soft, pliable, smooth-textured skin and flexible breastbone cartilage.']
label: ['broiler or fryer chicken']

iao_definition: ['A role is particular behaviour which a material entity may exhibit.']
label: ['role']

iao_definition: ['an organism that is the output of a genetic transformation process']
label: ['genetically modified organism']

iao_definition: ['An identifier is an information content entity that is the outcome of a dubbing process and is used to refer to one instance of entity shared by a group of people to refer to that individual entity.']
label: ['identifier']
['information biomacromolecule']
oio_related_synonym: ['genetically encoded biomacromolecules', 'genetically encoded biopolymers', 'information biomacromolecules', 'information biopolymers', 'information macromolecule', 'information macromolecules']

iao_definition: ['A class which contains food product categories qualified by a quality such as granularity or temperature, which is useful for tasks like food inspection where little prior knowledge of how the food came to be is available. Some terms like "food (frozen)" are both a quality descriptor and the output of a process.', 'The food product by quality class provides descriptors for describing food visually or via other senses, which is useful for tasks like food inspection where little prior knowledge of how the food came to be is available. Some terms like "food (frozen)" are both a quality descriptor and the output of a process.']
label: ['food product by quality']

iao_definition: ["A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to resist to a stimulus."]
label: ['resistance to']

iao_definition: ['the introduction. alteration or integration of genetic material into a cell or organism']
label: ['genetic transformation']

iao_definition: ['The directed movement of substances into the nucleus.']
oio_exact_synonym: ['nuclear import', 'single organism nuclear import', 'substance nuclear import']
label: ['import into nucleus']

iao_definition: ['An amino acid chain that is produced de novo by ribosome-mediated translation of a genetically-encoded mRNA, and any derivatives thereof.', 'An amino acid chain that is produced de novo by ribosome-mediated translation of a genetically-encoded mRNA.']
rdf_comment: ['The definition above excludes protein complexes, which some also consider a protein. Those who wish to refer to a class representing both senses of the word are directed to CHEBI:36080. Note that the definition allows for experimentally-manipulated genes, and allows for artifically-produced derivatives that mimic those found naturally. Proteins (in the sense defined here) that descended from a common ancestor can be classified into families and superfamilies composed of products of evolutionarily-related genes. The domain architecture of a protein is described by the order of its constituent domains. Proteins with the same domains in the same order are defined as homeomorphic [PRO:WCB].', 'Proteins descended from a common ancestor can be classified into families and superfamilies composed of products of evolutionarily-related genes. The domain architecture of a protein is described by the order of its constituent domains. Proteins with the same domains in the same order are defined as homeomorphic [PRO:WCB].']
label: ['protein']
